    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fortifications consisting of a wooden or stone keep built on a mound of raised earth and a bailey, surrounded by a palisade and ditch. This type of castle was used in Northern Europe from the 10th until the end of the 13th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
